# """
# CDEG-MSA: Counterfactual Disentangled Evidence Graph
# for multimodal sentiment analysis.
#
# This implementation follows the same coding style as the previous DMRL model,
# while keeping the new architecture independent from DMRL compatibility wrappers.
#
# Main design:
# 1. Modality-specific stems + shared Transformer encoder
# 2. Dynamic sparse causal evidence tokenizer
# 3. Tri-factor evidence disentanglement: sentiment / private / noise
# 4. Signed evidence graph with consensus / conflict / compensation relations
# 5. Node-level and edge-level counterfactual evidence calibration
# 6. Ordinal distribution head with predictive variance
#
# Inputs:
# - text:  if use_bert=True, shape [B, 3, Lt], where
#          text[:, 0, :] = input_ids,
#          text[:, 1, :] = attention_mask,
#          text[:, 2, :] = token_type_ids.
#          if use_bert=False, shape [B, Lt, Dt].
# - audio: [B, La, Da]
# - video: [B, Lv, Dv]
# - labels: [B] or [B, 1], continuous sentiment labels, e.g. in [-3, 3].
# """
#
